notes.name: rosefillings
notes.text:
Fillings

*Fillings*

You can also customise the contents of your message with contextual data. For example, you could mention a user by name in the welcome message, or mention them in a filter!

*Supported fillings*:
- `David`: The user's first name.
- `Blue`: The user's last name.
- `David Blue`: The user's full name.
- `@DavidBlue`: The user's username. If they don't have one, mentions the user instead.
- `David`: Mentions the user with their firstname.
- `233653652`: The user's ID.
- `Columbia Local`: The chat's name.
- `[Rules](buttonurl://t.me/MissRose_bot?start=rules_-1001227145846)`: Create a button to the chat's rules.
- : Enables link previews for this message. Useful when using links to Instant View pages.

*Example usages*:
- Save a filter using the user's name.
-> `/filter test David triggered this filter.`
- Add a rules button to a note.
-> `/save info Press the button to read the chat rules! [Rules](buttonurl://t.me/MissRose_bot?start=rules_-1001227145846)`
- Mention a user in the welcome message
-> `/setwelcome Welcome David to Columbia Local!`
